{
  "texts": [
    "Translating OT manuscripts remains a laborintensive task with limited scholarly resources.",
    "To the best of our knowledge, there is no MT system specifically designed for OT-to-English (OT-EN) translation.",
    "Current tools for Turkish-English translation are not directly adaptable for this task, despite Turkish being the most closely related living language to Ottoman.",
    "However, we know anecdotally that scholars in Ottoman studies have been using LLMs for translating their sources.",
    "Indeed, LLMs have the potential to act as first-pass translators of OT, reducing the time and effort needed to translate primary sources."
  ]
}